<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
  <head>
     <title>
         Bootstrap Typography
     </title>

     <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://maxcdn.bootstrapcdn.com/bootstrap/4.3.1/css/bootstrap.min.css">

      <script src="https://maxcdn.bootstrapcdn.com/bootstrap/4.3.1/js/bootstrap.min.js"></script>

    </head>
    <style>
      #bdy{
        background-color:rgb(223, 159, 159);
      }
      h1{
        color:azure;
      }
      .lead{
          color:aliceblue;
      }
      .fw-bold{
         color:antiquewhite;
      }
      .fst-italic{
         color:blanchedalmond;
      }
      #pr{
        color:aliceblue;
      }
    </style>
    <body id="bdy">
      <div class="container">
     <h1>
         Typography
     </h1>

     <p id="pr">This is a normal paragraph using Bootstrap typography.</p>

     <p class="lead">This is a lead paragraph. It looks bigger and important.</p>

     <p class="text-muted">This text looks muted.</p>

     <b class="fw-bold">This text is bold.</b><br><br>

     <i class="fst-italic">This text is italic.</i>
      <h1>Computer</h1> is an <mark>electronic device</mark> that processes data and gives output. 
     A computer follows instructions written in a <pre>programming language</pre>. 
      For example, a simple print command in <code>Python</code> can display text on the screen. 
     The term <abbr title="Central Processing Unit">CPU</abbr> is called the brain of the computer. 
     Many experts say: <blockquote>Computers make work faster and more accurate.</blockquote>
     </div>
  </body>
</html>
